

1. Top 10 IPs hitting a web server
   Command:
   awk '{print $1}' /var/log/nginx/access.log | sort | uniq -c | sort -nr | head -10

2. Find failed SSH login attempts in /var/log/auth.log
   Command:
   grep "Failed password" /var/log/auth.log | awk '{print $11}' | sort | uniq -c | sort -nr

3. Extract users who logged in last 24 hours
   Command:
   last -s -1days | awk '{print $1}' | sort | uniq

4. Count total number of error logs in the past week
   Command:
   grep -i "error" /var/log/app.log | grep "$(date --date='7 days ago' '+%b %d')" -A1000 | wc -l

5. Remove duplicate lines in a file
   Command:
   sort file.txt | uniq > file_unique.txt

6. Check if a process is running, start if not
   Command:
   pgrep -x nginx || systemctl start nginx

7. Kill processes consuming >80% CPU
   Command:
   ps -eo pid,%cpu --sort=-%cpu | awk '$2>80 {print $1}' | xargs -r kill -9

8. List top 5 memory-consuming processes
   Command:
   ps aux --sort=-%mem | head -6

9. Monitor if a service is active, restart if inactive
   Command:
   systemctl is-active --quiet myapp || systemctl restart myapp

10. Count number of processes owned by a user
    Command:
    ps -u username | wc -l

11. Alert if disk usage >90%
    Command:
    df -h | awk '$5+0>90 {print "Disk full: "$0}'

12. Find files >100MB in /var/log
    Command:
    find /var/log -type f -size +100M

13. Delete files older than 7 days
    Command:
    find /tmp -type f -mtime +7 -exec rm -f {} ;

14. Calculate disk usage of each directory in /home
    Command:
    du -sh /home/* | sort -h

15. Check inode usage
    Command:
    df -i

16. Ping multiple hosts and report unreachable
    Command:
    for host in google.com github.com yahoo.com; do ping -c1 $host &>/dev/null || echo "$host unreachable"; done

17. Count established TCP connections
    Command:
    ss -tn state established | wc -l

18. Check open ports for a process
    Command:
    lsof -i -P -n | grep nginx

19. Download file and retry if failed
    Command:
    curl -O [http://example.com/file](http://example.com/file) || curl -O [http://example.com/file](http://example.com/file)

20. Get public IP of server
    Command:
    curl -s [https://ipinfo.io/ip](https://ipinfo.io/ip)

21. Backup /var/log daily
    Command:
    tar -czf /backup/logs_$(date +%F).tar.gz /var/log

22. Rotate logs older than 30 days
    Command:
    find /var/log/myapp -type f -mtime +30 -exec gzip {} ;

23. Auto-clean temp files every hour
    Command:
    0 * * * * /usr/bin/find /tmp -type f -mtime +1 -delete

24. Sync directories using rsync
    Command:
    rsync -avz /var/www/html/ backup:/var/www/html/

25. Restart a service if log contains error
    Command:
    grep -q "CRITICAL" /var/log/app.log && systemctl restart myapp

26. Swap two numbers without temp variable
    Command:
    a=5; b=10
    a=$((a+b))
    b=$((a-b))
    a=$((a-b))

27. Check if a string is palindrome
    Command:
    read str
    [[ "$str" == "$(echo $str | rev)" ]] && echo "Palindrome"

28. Parse JSON using jq
    Command:
    cat file.json | jq '.data.id'

29. Count number of lines, words, characters
    Command:
    wc file.txt

30. Print last N lines containing keyword
    Command:
    grep "ERROR" /var/log/app.log | tail -10

31. Monitor CPU load and alert if >5
    Command:
    load=$(uptime | awk -F 'load average:' '{print $2}' | cut -d, -f1)
    awk -v l=$load 'BEGIN{if(l>5) print "High load:", l}'

32. Check if a port is in use
    Command:
    netstat -tuln | grep :8080

33. Automate user creation from a list
    Command:
   while read user; do
    id "$user" &>/dev/null || useradd "$user"
   done < users.txt

